A taxi and a truck were involved in a crash on the
N2 near the Richard's Bay off-ramp on Monday morning. "Netcare 911 responded to reports of a
collision on the N2 northbound about four kilometres from the Richard's Bay
offramp," Netcare 911 said. According to Netcare 911a total of four passengers sustained
injuries. "They were
treated on the scene by a Netcare 911 Advanced Life Support Paramedic" They were then transported by ambulance to a
hospital for further assessment and care.  